  "name": "devsecops-agency",
  "version": "0.3.7",
  "description": "A fully autonomous AI software-development company in a plugin. You speak only to the CEO; the CEO runs a board of 16 Chiefs; each Chief runs a council of specialists; specialists may, when work shards cleanly, spawn workers to run in parallel. Research-first, security-second, receipts-always. STRIDE + OWASP Top 10 baseline for code; OWASP ASI Top 10 2025 via the Red-Team Council; every shipped artifact gets SBOM + SLSA provenance; DLP on every outbound tool call; secrets only via vault refs; runtime-hook enforcement of commit-gate, secrets-scanner, tool-guardian, governance-audit, dependency-license-checker, session-logger. 1 CEO + 16 Chiefs + 75 specialists = 92 agents; Audit / Evaluation / Red-Team / SRE are informing + independent — never on any project's delivery path. v0.3.7 'Clarity' — pure restructure wave: 91 agent persona files moved from the flat agents/ tree into 16 per-council subfolders under agents/<council>/<agent>.md (ceo.md remains at root); Role Card v1 prepended to all 92 agents with uniform 8-field metadata (Council / Role / Reports to / Team / Model tier / Purpose / Convened by / Must not); 16 per-council TEAM.md roster cards added as the companion to each AGENTS.md contract; skills/fanout/ worker-tier scaffold declares the Chief → Specialist → Worker convention with 3-level depth cap (deeper requires council-lead ADR), parallelism caps (8/specialist, 24/council, 64/agency-wide), aggregation contracts, isolation under _workers/<specialist>/<shard>.md, and pairing with skills/taskflow/ via parent_task_id; README.md and AGENTS.md rewritten for clarity with wave history extracted to CHANGELOG.md. No new capabilities, no new runtime behaviour, no new tool grants — foundation wave for upcoming v0.3.8 Identity+Learning, v0.3.9 Rhythm+Career, v0.4.0 Governance+Resilience. Full wave-by-wave history (v0.2.0 → v0.3.6) is in CHANGELOG.md.",
